'''John Jympson''' was the editor of the "Lost Cut", the first edit of ''[[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|Star Wars]]''. [[George Lucas]] didn't like his work and he was fired, and the film was subsequently re-edited by editors [[Paul Hirsch]], [[Marcia Lucas]], and [[Richard Chew]] prior to release in [[1977]].<ref name="Insider 41">{{InsiderCite|41|The Evolution of Star Wars: Exploring the Lost Cut}}</ref>

